blocks.name: harinf
blocks.content: The Hartogs number of an infinite set is at least ` _om ` . _MOVABLE_ (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 10-Jul-2015.)

thm harinf(class c0, class c1) {
  |- wi(wa(wcel(c0, c1), wn(wcel(c0, cfn))), wss(com, cfv(char, c0)))
} = {
  ssrdv(hs0, com, cfv(char, c0), wa(wcel(c0, c1), wn(wcel(c0, cfn))))
  ex(wa(wcel(c0, c1), wn(wcel(c0, cfn))), wcel(cv(hs0), com), wcel(cv(hs0), cfv(char, c0)))
  sylanbrc(wa(wa(wcel(c0, c1), wn(wcel(c0, cfn))), wcel(cv(hs0), com)), wcel(cv(hs0), cfv(char, c0)), wcel(cv(hs0), con0), wbr(cv(hs0), cdom, c0))
  adantl(wa(wcel(c0, c1), wn(wcel(c0, cfn))), wcel(cv(hs0), com), wcel(cv(hs0), con0))
  nnon(cv(hs0))
  mpbird(wa(wa(wcel(c0, c1), wn(wcel(c0, cfn))), wcel(cv(hs0), com)), wbr(cv(hs0), cdom, c0), wn(wbr(c0, csdm, cv(hs0))))
  mtod(wa(wa(wcel(c0, c1), wn(wcel(c0, cfn))), wcel(cv(hs0), com)), wbr(c0, csdm, cv(hs0)), wcel(c0, cfn))
  simplr(wcel(c0, c1), wn(wcel(c0, cfn)), wcel(cv(hs0), com))
  syl2im(wa(wa(wcel(c0, c1), wn(wcel(c0, cfn))), wcel(cv(hs0), com)), wbr(c0, csdm, cv(hs0)), wcel(c0, cfn), wcel(cv(hs0), cfn), wbr(c0, cdom, cv(hs0)))
  sdomdom(c0, cv(hs0))
  ex(wcel(cv(hs0), cfn), wbr(c0, cdom, cv(hs0)), wcel(c0, cfn))
  domfi(cv(hs0), c0)
  syl2anc(wa(wa(wcel(c0, c1), wn(wcel(c0, cfn))), wcel(cv(hs0), com)), wb(wbr(cv(hs0), cdom, c0), wn(wbr(c0, csdm, cv(hs0)))), wcel(cv(hs0), cfn), wcel(c0, c1))
  adantl(wa(wcel(c0, c1), wn(wcel(c0, cfn))), wcel(cv(hs0), com), wcel(cv(hs0), cfn))
  nnfi(cv(hs0))
  simpll(wcel(c0, c1), wn(wcel(c0, cfn)), wcel(cv(hs0), com))
  fidomtri(cv(hs0), c0, c1)
  elharval(cv(hs0), c0)
  diff.hs0.c(com)
  diff.hs0.c(cfv(char, c0))
  diff.hs0.w(wa(wcel(c0, c1), wn(wcel(c0, cfn))))
}

thm harinf(class c0, class c1) {
  ‚ä¢ ((c0 ‚àà c1 ‚àß ¬¨ c0 ‚àà Fin)‚Üí _om ‚äÜ(har ` c0))
} = {
  ssrdv(hs0, com, (har ` c0), (c0 ‚àà c1 ‚àß ¬¨ c0 ‚àà Fin))
  ex((c0 ‚àà c1 ‚àß ¬¨ c0 ‚àà Fin), hs0 ‚àà _om, hs0 ‚àà(har ` c0))
  sylanbrc(((c0 ‚àà c1 ‚àß ¬¨ c0 ‚àà Fin)‚àß hs0 ‚àà _om), hs0 ‚àà(har ` c0), hs0 ‚àà On, hs0[‚âº]c0)
  adantl((c0 ‚àà c1 ‚àß ¬¨ c0 ‚àà Fin), hs0 ‚àà _om, hs0 ‚àà On)
  nnon(hs0)
  mpbird(((c0 ‚àà c1 ‚àß ¬¨ c0 ‚àà Fin)‚àß hs0 ‚àà _om), hs0[‚âº]c0, ¬¨ c0[‚â∫]hs0)
  mtod(((c0 ‚àà c1 ‚àß ¬¨ c0 ‚àà Fin)‚àß hs0 ‚àà _om), c0[‚â∫]hs0, c0 ‚àà Fin)
  simplr(c0 ‚àà c1, ¬¨ c0 ‚àà Fin, hs0 ‚àà _om)
  syl2im(((c0 ‚àà c1 ‚àß ¬¨ c0 ‚àà Fin)‚àß hs0 ‚àà _om), c0[‚â∫]hs0, c0 ‚àà Fin, hs0 ‚àà Fin, c0[‚âº]hs0)
  sdomdom(c0, hs0)
  ex(hs0 ‚àà Fin, c0[‚âº]hs0, c0 ‚àà Fin)

  adantl((c0 ‚àà c1 ‚àß ¬¨ c0 ‚àà Fin), hs0 ‚àà _om, hs0 ‚àà Fin)

blocks.name: wdom2d2
blocks.content: Deduction for weak dominance by a Cartesian product. _MOVABLE_ (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 10-Jul-2015.)

thm wdom2d2(setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, class c4, class c5, wff w0) {
  |- wi(w0, wbr(c0, cwdom, cxp(c1, c2)))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c0, c3))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c1, c4))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c2, c5))
  -| wi(wa(w0, wcel(cv(s0), c0)), wrex(s1, c1, wrex(s2, c2, wceq(cv(s0), c5))))
  -| diffss(s0, s1)
  -| diffss(s0, s2)
  -| diffss(s1, s2)
  -| diffsc(s0, c0)
  -| diffsc(s0, c1)
  -| diffsc(s0, c2)
  -| diffsc(s0, c5)
  -| diffsc(s1, c1)
  -| diffsc(s1, c2)
  -| diffsc(s2, c2)
  -| diffsw(s0, w0)
} = {
  wdom2d(s0, hs0, c0, cxp(c1, c2), c3, universe, csb(s1, cfv(c1st, cv(hs0)), csb(s2, cfv(c2nd, cv(hs0)), c5)), w0)
  xpexd(c1, c2, c4, c5, w0)
  sylibr(wa(w0, wcel(cv(s0), c0)), wrex(hs0, cxp(c1, c2), wceq(cv(s0), csb(s1, cfv(c1st, cv(hs0)), csb(s2, cfv(c2nd, cv(hs0)), c5)))), wrex(s1, c1, wrex(s2, c2, wceq(cv(s0), c5))))
  rexxpf(hs0, s1, s2, c1, c2, wceq(cv(s0), csb(s1, cfv(c1st, cv(hs0)), csb(s2, cfv(c2nd, cv(hs0)), c5))), wceq(cv(s0), c5))
  nfeq2(s1, cv(s0), csb(s1, cfv(c1st, cv(hs0)), csb(s2, cfv(c2nd, cv(hs0)), c5)))
  nfcsb1v(s1, cfv(c1st, cv(hs0)), csb(s2, cfv(c2nd, cv(hs0)), c5))
  nfeq2(s2, cv(s0), csb(s1, cfv(c1st, cv(hs0)), csb(s2, cfv(c2nd, cv(hs0)), c5)))
  nfcsb(s2, s1, cfv(c1st, cv(hs0)), csb(s2, cfv(c2nd, cv(hs0)), c5))
  nfcv(s2, cfv(c1st, cv(hs0)))
  nfcsb1v(s2, cfv(c2nd, cv(hs0)), c5)
  nfv(hs0, wceq(cv(s0), c5))
  eqeq2d(cv(s0), csb(s1, cfv(c1st, cv(hs0)), csb(s2, cfv(c2nd, cv(hs0)), c5)), c5, wceq(cv(hs0), cop(cv(s1), cv(s2))))
  csbopeq1a(s1, s2, cv(hs0), c5)
  diff.cxp.s(s0, c1, c2)
  diff.csb.s(s0, s1, cfv(c1st, cv(hs0)), csb(s2, cfv(c2nd, cv(hs0)), c5))
  diff.cfv.s(s0, c1st, cv(hs0))
  diff.c1st.s(s0)
  diff.csb.s(s0, s2, cfv(c2nd, cv(hs0)), c5)
  diff.cfv.s(s0, c2nd, cv(hs0))
  diff.c2nd.s(s0)
  diff.cv.s(s0, hs0)
  diffss.ex(s0, hs0)
  diff.hs0.s(s0)
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.c(cxp(c1, c2))
  diff.hs0.w(w0)
  diff.hs0.c(c1)
  diff.hs0.c(c2)
  diff.cv.s(s1, s0)
  diffss.ex(s1, s0)
  diff.cfv.s(s1, c1st, cv(hs0))
  diff.c1st.s(s1)
  diff.cv.s(s1, hs0)
  diffss.ex(s1, hs0)
  diff.hs0.s(s1)
  diff.cv.s(s2, s0)
  diffss.ex(s2, s0)
  diff.cfv.s(s2, c1st, cv(hs0))
  diff.c1st.s(s2)
  diff.cfv.s(s2, c2nd, cv(hs0))
  diff.c2nd.s(s2)
  diff.cv.s(s2, hs0)
  diffss.ex(s2, hs0)
  diff.hs0.s(s2)
  diff.hs0.w(wceq(cv(s0), c5))
}

thm wdom2d2(setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, class c4, class c5, wff w0) {
  ‚ä¢ (w0 ‚Üí c0[‚âº*](c1 √ó c2))
  ‚ä£ (w0 ‚Üí c0 ‚àà c3)
  ‚ä£ (w0 ‚Üí c1 ‚àà c4)
  ‚ä£ (w0 ‚Üí c2 ‚àà c5)
  ‚ä£ ((w0 ‚àß s0 ‚àà c0)‚Üí ‚àÉ(s1 ‚àà c1, ‚àÉ(s2 ‚àà c2, s0 = c5)))
  ‚ä£ d(s0, s1)
  ‚ä£ d(s0, s2)
  ‚ä£ d(s1, s2)
  ‚ä£ d(s0, c0)
  ‚ä£ d(s0, c1)
  ‚ä£ d(s0, c2)
  ‚ä£ d(s0, c5)
  ‚ä£ d(s1, c1)
  ‚ä£ d(s1, c2)
  ‚ä£ d(s2, c2)
  ‚ä£ d(s0, w0)
} = {
  wdom2d(s0, hs0, c0, (c1 √ó c2), c3, universe, [(1st ` hs0)/ s1][(2nd ` hs0)/ s2]c5, w0)
  xpexd(c1, c2, c4, c5, w0)
  sylibr((w0 ‚àß s0 ‚àà c0), ‚àÉ(hs0 ‚àà(c1 √ó c2), s0 =[(1st ` hs0)/ s1][(2nd ` hs0)/ s2]c5), ‚àÉ(s1 ‚àà c1, ‚àÉ(s2 ‚àà c2, s0 = c5)))
  rexxpf(hs0, s1, s2, c1, c2, s0 =[(1st ` hs0)/ s1][(2nd ` hs0)/ s2]c5, s0 = c5)
  nfeq2(s1, s0, [(1st ` hs0)/ s1][(2nd ` hs0)/ s2]c5)
  nfcsb1v(s1, (1st ` hs0), [(2nd ` hs0)/ s2]c5)
  nfeq2(s2, s0, [(1st ` hs0)/ s1][(2nd ` hs0)/ s2]c5)
  nfcsb(s2, s1, (1st ` hs0), [(2nd ` hs0)/ s2]c5)
  nfcv(s2, (1st ` hs0))
  nfcsb1v(s2, (2nd ` hs0), c5)
  nfv(hs0, s0 = c5)
  eqeq2d(s0, [(1st ` hs0)/ s1][(2nd ` hs0)/ s2]c5, c5, hs0 = < s1, s2 >)
  csbopeq1a(s1, s2, hs0, c5)
  diff.cxp.s(s0, c1, c2)
  diff.csb.s(s0, s1, (1st ` hs0), [(2nd ` hs0)/ s2]c5)
  diff.cfv.s(s0, c1st, hs0)
  diff.c1st.s(s0)
  diff.csb.s(s0, s2, (2nd ` hs0), c5)
  diff.cfv.s(s0, c2nd, hs0)
  diff.c2nd.s(s0)
  diff.cv.s(s0, hs0)
  diffss.ex(s0, hs0)
  diff.hs0.s(s0)
  diff.hs0.c(c0)
  diff.hs0.c((c1 √ó c2))
  diff.hs0.w(w0)
  diff.hs0.c(c1)
  diff.hs0.c(c2)
  diff.cv.s(s1, s0)
  diffss.ex(s1, s0)
  diff.cfv.s(s1, c1st, hs0)
  diff.c1st.s(s1)
  diff.cv.s(s1, hs0)
  diffss.ex(s1, hs0)
  diff.hs0.s(s1)
  diff.cv.s(s2, s0)
  diffss.ex(s2, s0)
  diff.cfv.s(s2, c1st, hs0)
  diff.c1st.s(s2)
  diff.cfv.s(s2, c2nd, hs0)
  diff.c2nd.s(s2)
  diff.cv.s(s2, hs0)
  diffss.ex(s2, hs0)
  diff.hs0.s(s2)
  diff.hs0.w(s0 = c5)
}

blocks.name: fnwe2lem2
blocks.content: Lemma for ~ fnwe2 . An element which is in a minimal fiber and minimal within its fiber is minimal globally; thus ` T ` is well-founded. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 19-Jan-2015.)

blocks.name: fnwe2
blocks.content: A well-ordering can be constructed on a partitioned set by patching together well-orderings on each partition using a well-ordering on the partitions themselves. Similar to ~ fnwe but does not require the within-partition ordering to be globally well. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 19-Jan-2015.)
blocks.origin:

blocks.name: aomclem1
blocks.content: Lemma for ~ dfac11 . This is the beginning of the proof that multiple choice is equivalent to choice. Our goal is to construct, by transfinite recursion, a well-ordering of ` ( R1 `` A ) ` . In what follows, ` A ` is the index of the rank we wish to well-order, ` z ` is the collection of well-orderings constructed so far, ` dom z ` is the set of ordinal indices of constructed ranks i.e. the next rank to construct, and ` y ` is a postulated multiple-choice function. Successor case 1, define a simple ordering from the well-ordered predecessor. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 18-Jan-2015.)

blocks.name: dfac11
blocks.content: The right-hand side of this theorem (compare with ~ ac4 ), sometimes known as the "axiom of multiple choice", is a choice equivalent. Curiously, this statement cannot be proved without ~ ax-reg , despite not mentioning the cumulative hierarchy in any way as most consequences of regularity do. This is definition (MC) of [Schechter] p. 141. _EDITORIAL_: the proof is not original with me of course but I lost my reference sometime after writing it. A multiple choice function allows any total order to be extended to a choice function, which in turn defines a well-ordering. Since a well-ordering on a set defines a simple ordering of the power set, this allows the trivial well-ordering of the empty set to be transfinitely bootstrapped up the cumulative hierarchy to any desired level. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 20-Jan-2015.) (Revised by Stefan O'Rear, 1-Jun-2015.)

blocks.name: kelac1
blocks.content: Kelley's choice, basic form: if a collection of sets can be cast as closed sets in the factors of a topology, and there is a definable element in each topology (which need not be in the closed set - if it were this would be trivial), then compactness (via finite intersection) guarantees that the final product is nonempty. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 22-Feb-2015.)
